reviews.review_text: eh kinda crappy quality but some songs are worth it

Raunchy! Thanx Leon and Charlie.  Leon is a true visionary.  What a job.  This is a good sounding audience for the time.  Crank it up, it has a nasty garage band sound the boys could have at this time.  Sounded good through my old Boston Acoustic floor speakers but would have benefited from an eq.  
Nice to hear Pig play harp on a song he doesn't sing and It's a Sin is a bit of a rarity.  Nice jams throughout, particularly out of China Cat and the second Cryptical.  The Dark Star is plain evil with a brief hint at Playing.  A must listen.  Unless you are a sound freak you need to at least check this out.  I am playing It Hurts Me thru Doin' That Rag on my radio show this week.  Peace

great 69 4.5 for the show 3.5 for sound quality.
Cryptical>Dark Star is a highlight...the Eleven cut is harsh
Main Ten At around 17:25 into the Dark Star there is a distinct Main Ten/Playing jam. Very wild...
Dark star Love this show the dark star is yelling at you. I would to go back in time to see them do a song with that much power. Forever  grateful
